page.title: 08WILDLIFE IN FENDRAYTON FEN
page.content: {Fendrayton Fen}is mostly farmland though some of it is disused gravel pits. The gravel pits being disused are now overgrown and attract lots of wild birds and mammals. When I went up there I saw plenty of{Wigeon}and{Moorhens}on the pits. In the middle of one of the pits there is an island with a{Silver {Birch Tree}on it:up the birch tree, roosting there were{Lapwings. When I was there in February I saw two{Foxes}a male and a female.February is the end of the mating season for foxes so about July their cubs are just going out into the wild. Another time I was there with my dad (at night)in the car we swung around the corner fast and saw all these rabbits running away from the lights. I think the{wild life of the fen} is very varied and interesting.
